<br>
From my perspective, I think the DPS of mobs in PoP along with the insane Exp that they give in a way makes Soloing more preferable than Grouping. While I think soloing is bad for the game entirely, I have less of a problem with classes like Wizards or Necros doing so because they are not as &quot;uniquely preferred&quot; as Enchanters are in many Exp group situations. Without Enchanters, many places become much more difficult to the point of impossibility.<br>
<br>
If we can get a contract that says &quot;All Enchanters must group regardless of how much more Exp Charm soloing will yield,&quot; THEN I would be perfectly happy if Command of Druzzil remained the same.<br>
<br>
Obviously such a contract can't exist, and unfortunately for grouping classes like us, we rely on others for progression. I suppose if Charm will take away the potential group partners we have, then perhaps give another class something that is equitable as compensation. Mages now have Elemental Mez. Give Mages Elemental Slow to compensate for not having an Enchanter that can do both. Then, we can bring our own groups to places where Elemental Mobs exist.<br>
<br>
YES, I realize the &quot;slow&quot; thing is a dead horse and I don't think that this is the correct solution, but I'm restating it as a possible solution. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60465">Xerphanis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tiiden>Tiiden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#333333>(1/14/03 10:40:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=408.topic&index=142>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Massive Changes on test</span><hr size=1> It is my opinion that anyone who is complaining about the nerfed charm is just mad because they can no longer level up at an unreasonably high rate - there is no reason to complain otherwise. CoD was so overpowered that it made obsolete any damage dealing class, except in certain rare circumstances (i.e. totally broke the game). I also don't think any post on any message board caused the nerf, Sony would have noticed sooner or later - they do play the game you know. Personally I would have preferred they tacked on a recast time equal to max. duration, but something had to be done.<br>
<br>
Low level charms could be considered overpowered as well (I was able to level a non-twinked enchanter from 12-17 in NK at 1hr/level solo; however you can level even faster in PC with a group lol), but I belive there is suffient risk involved in using the low level ones (where it costs big money to keep yourself constantly runed/sow'd). I'm playing an un-twinked lv 27 enchanter currently, and it is almost certian death to use charm+haste without sow/rune unless you can stay on your toes the entire time.<br>
<br>
In summery, listen to Noonie, and quit crying! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Tiiden VandorGriffin<br>
