<br>
I cut <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Noonie</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a far amount of slack, because she usually brings pretty good arguments to the table, even though she too often slips into flame mode.<br>
<br>
This subject is still generating <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">way</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> too much emotion.<br>
<br>
Although <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Noonie</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is not alone, I need to be specific: your content to emotion ratio is getting way too low.  Especially considering your volume and your activism, it is incumbent upon you to watch your tongue.<br>
<br>
I too feel a great a deal of emotion.  I even sometimes feel like those that disagree with me are perhaps being intellectually dishonest when they push arguments that any educated person would recognize as being weak.  But I have learned to avoid that implication, and attack the argument, not the arguer.<br>
<br>
I am locking this bad boy down.<br>
<br>
Let's try to take a day off from this subject, and get some emotional distance.<br>
<br>
